npc.andrew.0: This game is still under heavy development, don't forget to check the §aforums§r often for updates!
npc.andrew.1: If you'd like to discuss SkyBlock with other players then check out the SkyBlock section of the §aforums§f!
npc.duke.0: Are you new here? As you can see there is a lot to explore!
npc.duke.1: My advice is to start by visiting the §bFarm§r, or the §bCoal Mine§r both North of here.
npc.duke.2: If you do need some wood, the best place to get some is West of the §bVillage§r!
npc.felix.0: You can access your §aEnder Chest§r in your §aSkyBlock Menu§r.
npc.felix.1: Store items in this chest and access them at any time!
npc.leo.0: You can unlock §aLeaflet Armor§r by progressing through your §aOak Log Collection§r.
npc.lep.1: There is a §bForest§r west of the §bVillage§r where you can gather Oak Logs.
npc.leo.2: To check your Collection progress and rewards, open the §aCollection Menu§r in your §aSkyBlock Menu§r.
npc.liam.0: One day those houses in the §bVillage§r will be rentable for Coins!
npc.liam.1: Anyone will be able to rent them, players, co-ops, even Guilds!
npc.lynn.0: If you ever get lost during a quest, open your §bQuest Log§r in your §aSkyBlock Menu§r!
npc.jack.0: Your §2SkyBlock Profile§r in your §2SkyBlock Menu§r shows details about your current stats!
npc.jack.1: There are 7 stats in total, including §4â�¤ Health§r, §4â�� Strength§r, and §2â�ˆ Defense§r.
npc.jack.2: Equipped armor, weapons, and accessories in your inventory all improve your stats.
npc.jack.3: Additionally, leveling your Skills can permanently boost some of your stats!
npc.jamie.0: You might have noticed that you have a Mana bar!
npc.jamie.1: Some items have mysterious properties, called Abilities.
npc.jamie.2: Abilities use your Mana as a resource. Here, take this Rogue Sword. I don't need it!
npc.tom.0: I will teach you the Promising Axe Recipe to get you started!
npc.tom.1: All SkyBlock recipes can be found by opening the Recipe Book in your SkyBlock Menu.
npc.ryu.1: Farming, Mining, Foraging, Fishing, Combat, Enchanting, Alchemy, Carpentry and Runecrafting.
npc:ryu.2: You can learn all about them in the Skill Menu, located in your SkyBlock Menu.
npc.stella.0: At any time you can create a Co-op with your friends!
npc.stella.1: Simply go in your SkyBlock Menu where you can find the Profile Menu.
npc.stella.2: This is where you can create, delete or switch SkyBlock Profiles.
npc.stella.3: Enter /coop followed by the name of all the friends you want to invite!
npc.stella.4: All your friends have to be online to accept!
npc.vex.welcome.0: You can shift click any player to trade with them!
npc.vex.welcome.1: Once both players are ready to trade, click on Accept trade!
npc.vex.welcome.2: Make sure you don't give away all of your belongings!
npc.vex.interract: Shift then click on me to Trade!
npc.vex.general.0: You can disable Player Trading your SkyBlock Settings!
npc.vex.general.1: Your settings can found in the SkyBlock Menu
npc.seraphine.general.1: Contribute to community projects, upgrade your account, and more by talking to Elizabeth!
npc.seraphine.no_mayor: The Mayor Elections are currently closed but come back later and check them out!
npc.seraphine.mayor: You can also vote in the mayor elections by heading through the warp upstairs!
npc.bea.0: Hello! Do you have a pet?
npc.bea.1: Pets are little companions for your adventures in SkyBlock!
npc.bea.2: Personally, I prefer the bee pet!
npc.george.0: Hey there, I'm George the Pet Collector!
npc.george.1: I travel the world searching far and wide for the rarest of pets I can find!
npc.george.2: If you have any pets which need a new home I'd be happy to buy them off you!
npc.zog.0: Hello! Have you heard of pet items?
npc.zog.1: Pet items give your companions bonuses!
npc.zog.2: I sell all kinds of pet items if you'd like to try one out!
npc.blacksmith.welcome.0: I'm the town Blacksmith! I can reforge items for you, for a price.
npc.blacksmith.welcome.1: Reforging usually costs Coins, but since I'm feeling friendly I can reforge your first item for 10 Coal.
npc.blacksmith.welcome.2: Go into the Mine to collect Coal and return to learn how to reforge items!
npc.blacksmith.complete.1: Reforging item allows you to get the most out of your weapons, armor, and other items by applying stat modifiers to them!
npc.blacksmith.complete.2: To reforge an item, place an item in my inventory. Reforging costs Coins - the more prestigious items cost more to reforge!
npc.blacksmith.complete.3: However, this time I will reforge any item for the low price of 10 coal!
npc.marco.welcome.1: I'm a world-famous artist to be. Most people just call me "the new da Vinci."
npc.marco.welcome.2: Unfortunately, I ran out of dye this morning...
npc.marco.welcome.3: In my garden are some flowers. Could you pick 5 Dandelions and turn them into Rose Red Dye, then bring them back to me?
npc.marco.quest.0: Wow! That's the most beautiful red dye I have ever seen!
npc.marco.quest.2: You can select a spray by left-clicking your Spray Can!
npc.marco.quest.3: Right-click any wall on your private island to spray it. If you ever lose your Spray Can, you can craft another one using the recipe in your Recipe Book!
npc.marco.quest.4: Thank you so much for your help. You should visit me in my Canvas Room sometime! Step into the portal to the left over there!
npc.marco.complete.0: Before spraying on a wall, consider previewing it in the menu! Right-click on any spray of your choice and it'll magically appear in your hand.
Don't forget to refill your spray can with dye! You can pick some of the flowers in my garden if you want to.
You can select sprays by left-clicking with your Spray Can!
